< review>
The amenities here are outstanding and the apartments are nice, but the lack of security made this property a hard no go when looking at places for our daughter.  The property isn't gated so any and everyone can walk onto it. There is no onsite security either. During our tour a homeless guy rode his bike right through the parking lot and we saw another homeless guy wandering near the property as we left.

Side note:  I know you have to explain the options to qualify to rent here.  However when someone tells you their credit is fine, MOVE ON TO YOUR NEXT POINT. I don't need to hear "Well just in case. . ."  and keep reiterating how to qualify if your credit is bad.  It's insulting.<//review>

<review>I have been living here over two years. The reason l choose here is because of short distance to campus.
The buildings and surrounding areas are quite beautiful and clean because every staff here is working very hard to help residents have a better life. And also the leasing office have a group of very kind and friendly officers working for us. Some of them are also Sac students. Another shining spot is that here have the best clubhouse compare with other communities which include study area, gym, coffee corner and so on. Besides that, I really glad here provides the Envoy electric car for rent which is super cheap and convenient.
However, no place is perfect. Some bad things happened sometimes from all aspects. Crazy party, and random people coming inside. < Text>
Okay here is a brutally honest review of the Crossings Student Apartments. I've lived here for over a year & I can realistically say that this is the nicest apartment complex in Sacramento for the price. I do believe that many of the issues you may read in other reviews have occurred due to lack of respect of many of the residents/friends of residents that live here, however recently under new management there have been no issues at all & seems like things have been addressed accordingly (as far as guest policies, security presence, parking etc.)

As a resident I understand how busy staff can get & I know they do the best that they possibly can to get their work done. I have had nothing but positive interactions with the staff & management & recently was able to set up an appointment with the property manager to fix an issue with my account which she promptly resolved. I simply just had to send her an email & my appointment was the next day.

As busy and hard working as the staff can get, I know they do not have the time to fix some of minor issues some residents may have. But I genuinely do enjoy living here & can say that the majority of the residents here are very pleasant & friendly.

I would 10/10 recommend this apartment complex to anyone who may be going to Sacramento State (or surrounding schools/job) come Spring/Summer 2021.

By the way, you will not find a better fitness center at any complex in the Sacramento area.</Text>

<username>Claudia Johnson</username>< text>
I‚Äôve been tutoring ESL students for over 15 years. I fell in love with it during my AmeriCorps service from 2000-2002 in Santa Rosa. When I moved to San Diego, I supplemented my income as a stay at home mom with tutoring ESL students across the city. I‚Äôve worked with Alliant International University, Education First, and Connect English students and have noticed over the years that Connect English students demonstrate the biggest improvement over time. Their retention rate is noticeably highest of all my clients. Their accents, spelling, punctuation, grammar and even use of colloquialisms show marked improvements that build upon themselves. I care about all the clients I work with, but I notice myself consistently looking forward to time with Connect English students. They are simply the happiest bunch of clients that I work with. And the most fun, and funny! Somehow, Connect English provides an education not just in the proper use of the English language, but also in socializing with native English speakers. It‚Äôs hard enough to master an entirely new language, let alone be able to make your tutor laugh so hard she cries. My only wish is that Connect English would offer summer language camps for English-speaking schoolchildren, so that my child could reap the benefits of such a comprehensive learning experience.</text>

<review>(Translated by Google) I have studied in the Connect English language school for more than two years. I learned English from Level 2 to the TOEFL class, and successfully applied to the university I want to go to.

I think the learning here is the most cost-effective in SAN DIEGO, the tuition is cheap, the teachers are professional, academic rigorous and standardized, but it is very user-friendly. In addition to learning, there are many activities here to help students from all over the world understand and learn about culture and customs from all angles. It integrates entertainment and learning. If there are fees, it is also a discount for students, which is very cost-effective.

In short, Connect English language school gave me a very good learning experience, and I highly recommend this school.

<text>(Translated by Google) I had a good experience at Connect English school. The teachers are well prepared and the textbooks are very good. The staff seems to be a bit clumsy and not always very present, but they all have a good positive energy that I enjoyed. The course is not very difficult so I think it's ideal for those who are starting out, but if you already know how to speak English well maybe you can look for something a little more challenging. My classmates who did not speak any English say the classes are very good. I paid for my entire course in Brazil so I did not have any problems, but some of my classmates pointed out that the school finances are very annoying as well. <text>I have eaten in top rated fine dining restaurants as well as hole in the wall dives. I enjoy a wide range of ethnic foods. This was my second and LAST visit to this business. I really wanted to like it as I try to support small family businesses.
I ordered jasmine tea with dinner. It was concentrated (for their boba drinks). I told the young girl it was too strong and I could not drink it. She said "I'll  water it down". I watched as she poured half out and refilled with hot water. This is not how you make a pot of jasmine tea. Needless to say, I still could not drink it. I was not asked what else I wanted, nor offered anything else to drink besides my water.
BTW, I  only saw 2 young girls in the front of the restaurant and 1 of age man from the kitchen the whole time I was there. No experienced,  adults were present.
When my dinner arrived (the same dish I ordered the time before) it had a very foul odor. My instincts told me not to eat it. When asked if I needed anything, I told the young girl that there was something not right about the food. She just walked away. I finished my egg rolls and went to the desk to pay. When asked if everything was good, I said no, it wasn't and explained that there was something definitely wrong with the food. I told her that I would pay for what I had eaten, but not for the rest. < review>
As a Vietnamese person who moved here from Mira Mesa, I was excited to see a new Vietnamese restaurant open in the area. There are a lot of authentic Vietnamese dishes here, besides pho which is nice to see. Highly recommended and stoked they're finally open! Their hours are 930a-9p, 7 days a week.

I have had their banh mi (Vietnamese sandwich) and I highly recommend the bbq pork. It's delicious and filling for less than $5. Their egg rolls are also nice and dense. The pho broth is good and doesn't taste watered down like some other places in the area. If you like a lot of meat in your pho, I'd suggest adding extra.

The customer service is fantastic. They made us feel very welcome and they're attentive to our questions and order customizations. I will definitely be coming here regularly.<//review>

< review>
I have read so many reviews here stating what great customer service they have , not true in my case, it was terrible, especially from a ms. Rainey. After posting a past due payment for my aunt that wound up in the hospital from a heartattack, we were not given access to my aunts unit so that we may remove her belongings before the next months payment. Ms. Rainey never updated the notes on the account to allow us access. She was all to happy to take our money but did little else to make this an easier process. She even had the nerve to suggest that we go to the hospital and take a selfie with my aunt giving a thumbs up. They also asked to speak to her,  even tho we told them she could not because she has a trache in her throat. After having the woman at the counter get ms. Rainey on the phone, she said she would not change anything on the account, and that we need to come back tomorrow and when she is in the office. After explaining that my mother was made executive to my aunts estate when she was admitted to the hospital the woman at the counter said she would talk to their lawyers and see what they have to say. Well after waiting in the parking lot for 20 minutes with an angry mother the woman at the counter came out and said they would give us access if we had a key to the unit which we did. Overall a terrible experience , the woman at the counter was helpful but ms. Rainey needs to work on her customer service.
P.S. , I don't know what they have going on at this facility but there seems to be a lot of people hanging out at the facility. I mean they weren't loading or unloading anything, they seem to loiter and do repairs to cars in the middle of the aisles. I even witnessed one of these people bring in 2 cartons of eggnog and asked that the woman at the counter store it for him in the refrigerator, then go into the bathroom with two other people, I'm  going to take a wild guess and suggest they are homeless and probably live in their unit, and it seems to be permitted by this facility. I will be calling corporate and filing a complaint .</review>

< text>
I take my dogs here every time I leave town and they do a good job looking after them. My dogs are excited to go there which I see as a good sign and clearly like the staff. The prices are good and I've never had a problem. I take my dogs about once per month on average. I recommend to friends.

A lot of reviews are decrying the grooming - I don't get my dogs groomed here. I typically bathe them after a stay. It is an outdoor kennel after all, and dogs smell after being outside. They have coverage from the sun for shade and misters, and there are houses to insulate if it's cold.< /text>

<date>1559088251048< /date><rate>1<//rate>< text>
If I could post zero stars I would. I usually don't post negative reviews but when a business owner is dishonest I think people deserve to know. I came to Le's to get a dress altered on Thursday and asked when will it be ready by and he answered early next week. I told him can it be early Monday because i'm flying back home and he said okay that works and even circled Monday on the paper receipt. Monday comes and I drive all the way back and the store is closed! I then send my sister today to go and explain the situation and then mail the dress to me (more money out of my pocket) and he claims that he said it'll be ready Saturday but because I wanted it to be Monday he circled Monday. My sister told him why would you circle Monday and tell her okay Monday when you were going to be closed? He said because I was following her request she didn't want Saturday (which is a bold faced lie). I'm completely shocked by the blatant dishonesty and will never come back here again. STAY AWAY!<//text>

<gmap_id>0x80c3314c774b00c3:0x3d1ab937d58ec85a<//gmap_id><Time>1552793643998</Time>< Text>
Been here a several times for tire maintenance and oil changes, and the service is excellent! 1st time I had took my car to another shop to get a flat repair and they told me I would need a new tire. Took to this Pep Boys and they fixed it for $10. Today I did an oil change and another flat repair. 4 hours later the tire that was repaired was flat again. Took it back 10 minutes before closing and they re-checked it. Turns out there was a second nail they missed or I have the worst luck and managed to drive over a nail on the tire I just got fixed (I wouldn't doubt it). Regardless they patched that hole up free of charge even though it was past closing and they had to stay a bit longer to do it. Best place I've been to in a long time and will definitely be bringing my vehicle here as long as I live in the area. Thanks again Anthony!

On a side note: If you can, be sure to call and setup an appointment as they can get pretty busy at times and you can avoid having to wait hours or coming back at a later time.</Text>

<review>I bought tires from Pep Boys about a year ago, so brought my truck into the Upland shop to have the tires rotated because they were starting to show uneven wear and I was leaving on a driving vacation in two days. I also had a slow leak I wanted repaired.

The guy behind the counter said that there‚Äôd be no charge, even though I offered to pay. I left my truck there for the day and picked it up close to closing later that evening.

I didn‚Äôt drive it much, only locally, until I left for vacation. I found that, after a few freeway miles, that there was something seriously wrong with the truck‚Äôs ride.

I pulled into a tire shop in Needles, CA and told the owner/tech there about the symptoms. The truck was vibrating so badly that the dashboard looked like it was going to fall off.

He removed and balanced and replaced each tire. He found that a) the tires had not been rotated and b) the tires had been balanced incorrectly. Weights had been put on the complete opposite side of the imbalance, or on the inside of the tire instead of the outside. In one instance 5 ounces of weights had been added to balance out 5.5 ounces of weight, where only .5 ounces were necessary.

I gladly paid the man $50 for the work he performed and then got back on the freeway with a smooth and perfect ride.

Later I went back to Pep Boys Upland to talk about the lousy service. The same guy was behind the counter, and first he implied that I was lying, then that the Needles tech was lying, then he said that the shops tire-balancing machine was old and defective, then he said that the tech who performed the work was new and inexperienced. He promised that the service manager would call me, but he never did.

1580948464377</Time>
<Name>Calahan Miller</Name>< review>
We had a complete HVAC installed last June; 3T Unit, all new duct work, relocation of two and addition of one more ceiling vents and a complimentary Nest thermostat ... three days ago our heat wasn't working consistent with how we set the temp on the thermostat and then this morning it wasn't heating at all.  I called early in the morning and they were able to put me on the schedule for today. (BTW - I've never had a company keep in touch on the status of their arrival more, or better, than JW does!)

Christian came out to diagnose the problem - and wouldn't you know .... the heat came on!!!!???!!! I talked him through all the *symptoms* of what had been going on, he asked questions and then went to looking for any irregularities with the system. He did his best, but -since the heat was now working- he was hard pressed to find a culprit. He did take off and clean a sensor, which he says sometime can be an issue, though he didn't feel strongly that it was in this case, but it didn't hurt to do at least that just in case (an appreciated show of good faith on his part, for sure). Anyway, so in the absence of any findings to the issue, which was now a non-issue, Christian left. He, however assured me should it fail again do not hesitate to call them back out - they want to make it right! He also let me know something I did not know - in the event that the system fails again, not to shut it off completely, to simply adjust the settings to allow the system to go into stand-by so they can read any error codes from the unit.

In all my years of being a homeowner I can say when you find a service company that follows through, stands behind their equipment and labor and commits to making it right then you stay with that company. JW Heating and Air is that company for me! This is my second unit install and services with JW, we had a new system put in our son's condo as well, and every time; be it scheduling with the office personnel, meeting and working with a sales person, or meeting with a technician, they have always made me feel like a valued customer.

Thank you Christian, and thank you JW Heating & Air ... again!< /review>

<userid>113884349009930363904</userid><username>sam sperling< /username><date>1591230438300< /date><rating>5</rating>< Text>
Extremely pleased with JW Plumbing from start to "finish."  Michael Campbell, the JW Customer Rep was knowledgeable, professional, and a nice guy.  He was very thorough in explaining what work would be required, the equipment that would provided (with options and recommendations), and provided two quotes- one if the new A/C unit could be installed near the existing unit and the second if the new A/C unit had to be moved to the back of the house depending upon where our property line was.
Although JW was not the cheapest quote that I got, Michael explained that JW employees were highly trained and long time, bonded employees; all equipment provided were of high quality- e.g., Lennox A/C and Heater; and that City inspectors would certify their work.  (Michael said JW Heating & Air will only do a job the right way.)  The price was a little less painful after Michael indicated that Costco would provide a 10% gift card, and we would also be eligible to receive a couple more discounts/rebates.
Michael left me his business card, company brochure, information of the Lennox equipment that would be installed, and a copy of the work order.
The next day, Steven, the manager of the installation teams came by to inspect our premise to make sure the installers would have everything they would need to complete the job in two days.  Steven was very professional, personable, and reassuring.
First thing Monday morning 7 A.M., Steven introduced me to Ramon, the team leader of the installation crew, and a couple of the people who would be installing the HVAC system.  Ramon and his crew were great.  They were extremely, extremely polite and humble, efficient, quiet, and neat and hard working.  They covered the floor with tarp, cleaned-up at the end of the day, and were tidy during the day.  After the crew was done for the day at 3:30 P.M. , my wife  pointed out a number of problem that she found, e.g., a crack in the ceiling, a gap around the a/c pipe outside, and a couple of light switches that were not working now.
The next morning, Ramon and his crew were at the house at 7 A.M. again ready to work.  I talked to Ramon about the problems that my wife had discovered the previous day.  Ramon was polite, listened patiently, and said in a very reassuring tone that they would take care of them (which they did).  Again, his crew was very polite, efficient, and neat.  By 3:30 the crew had finished their work and left.  Again, they cleaned up everything, inside and outside the house. The work looked beautiful.  Very clean and professional.  (The entire process from start, first call, to "finish", installation, took only one week.)
Ramon stayed behind to make sure the HVAC system was working properly and explain how to operate the new system.  The a/c worked perfectly.  The heater, unfortunately, would not come on.  Ramon worked on the heater for one and a half hours, but could not fix the problem despite calling the office.  JW called me later that day and said they would send someone in the morning to look at the heater.
The next morning, Steven (the manager of the installation crew) came by to inspect the heater. Steven said he thinks the problem is a defective part and explained the function of the part.   Steven said this was the second a/c unit in 20 units they had installed that had this problem. Because this was a new unit, he was hopeful that they would get the replacement part and be able to fix the problem by next week and of course there would be no charge.
Although the job is not "finished," I am confident that JW will fix the problem.  (I'm just glad that it's the heater that is not working and not the a/c!.)  The primary reason, my wife and I went with JW Heating & Air is because they are a Costco vendor.  Based upon my dealing with JW,  I am glad that we did.

Jack
Monterey Park, CA< /Text>

I called JW Heating and Air to have our A/C inspected, tuned up, charged up, etc. because it felt as though the cool air was not as cool as it once was.
I was surprised to get an appointment within 3 days even though we are in the middle of a punishing heatwave.
Angel was the technician who showed up
- early by 5 minutes - and devoted six hours to caring for our 3 A/C units.  Angel was very knowledgeable & kept me in the loop as he progressed through the house.  He had every part he needed on his truck so there was no time lost chasing down parts - a pet peeve of mine.  In the end, it was not cheap but you get what you pay for and I am more than pleased that I've got functioning, efficient A/C units again.
I will definitely use JW Heating and Air in the future - and I will ask for Angel to be the technician.</Text>

< Review>
A week ago I called for service to check out what I thought might be a problem with my recently installed heating system. The service representative could find nothing wrong and left. A few days later, when I went to the basement where the equipment was housed, I noticed that the face of the heater had not been put back. Since it was a simple matter to do, I put it back myself. I also noticed water leaking from the heater so I called JW and told them the problem. They promptly sent out Victor D later the same day. He noticed immediately that the plug from the water pump had been pulled out of the wall socket and that was why water was leaking from the heater instead of going into the pump. He also took the time to explain various functions of the heater installation. Although I was disappointed in the prior service call and its result (i.e. leaving the pump plug disconnected and not replacing the heater face), my confidence in JW was more than restored by Victor's attitude, knowledge and general demeanor. Victor represents the best kind of service representative and JW should be glad he is in its employ.<//Review>

<Rating>5</Rating><text>I'm in the process of doing a total gut and renovation of my condo.  The team from JW Heating and Air installed new duct work and an air conditioning unit on the roof (new air handler and fan will be after the drywall is installed).

My experience started by meeting with Ted who worked with us to define the system that would best fit our needs.  He also helped us to come up with a duct solution that allowed us to relocate some ducts in order to raise a ceiling in the hallway and master bedroom area.  Ted was very courteous and always prompt in answering questions or meeting at the unit as we refined the design.  I couldn't ask for a better consultant!.

Shawn, Ramon, and Ignacio were our installers.  Phase 1 was scheduled for 2 days and they completed it on time.  All three team members were extremely personable and clearly knew what they were doing.  They arrived early both days in order to start promptly.  With a total gut of the unit, dust is bad.  However they wore "booties" when leaving the unit to prevent dust from getting on the hallway carpets.  I was doing other work in the unit while they were working and there was never an issue with me being there.  The installation far exceeds my expectations, and all debris was promptly cleaned up and removed from the unit throughout the work day and at the end of the day.

It was an absolute pleasure working with the JW Heating and Air team.<//text>< pics>

<Name>Bella Kapp< /Name><rating>5< /rating>< review>
After several attempts to diagnosis the problem with my dad's A/C unit, Joshua W. was knowledgeable and professional in relaying to us what the problem was and why we kept experiencing lack of cooling with our unit several times within a short period of time intervals.   He informed us honestly what would need to be done to rectify the problem.  He was pleasant, did not rush and truly wanted to do a thorough job. He sealed the coil that had a leak in it and informed us that it may or may not hold.   Since the problem was occurring way before our warranty had expired,  JW honored replacement of the coil that was causing the problem.  They pursued us in setting up an appt to do the work to replace the coil.  No sooner than the coil was replaced, we experienced dripping water from a crack in the ceiling.  Josh came out again and diagnosed that there was an opening in the drain pan that would need to be sealed.  He also cleared the over flow pipe so make sure it was clear since we never experienced water dripping outside the house from this pipe since the installation of the unit.  The overflow pipe had been installed flush with the wall of the house so that the dripping was now being directed onto the porch and wall of the house.  Josh had to be called out again to extend the pipe away from the contact of the house.  It is now working satisfactorily.  The company still has to repair the crack in the ceiling and we are awaiting resolution with that problem.  Throughout this entire ordeal we are so impressed with Josh W. and his professionalism as well as Denise in the office.  Denise would call us back during a holiday weekend and even when the office was closed during the weekend.  They were exceptional people to work with and we always felt that our problems and concerns were given immediate priority and attention.  We would highly recommend Josh W. as your technician and Denise as your go to person in the office..  You will not be sorry!<//review>

< text>
In calling Costco's third-party HVAC servicer, JW Heating & Air, I was very specific with the receptionist that I had already arranged to have Home Depot install my HVAC system, but would consider one last quote if JW could match or beat the price. I informed the receptionist that I needed a 3 ton Lennox heating and ac unit, insulation added, installation, and all new ducts (with permits) to be either $13,500 or lower. After putting me on hold for about 10 minutes, and speaking with an adviser, the receptionist guaranteed they could get close or beat it. Accordingly, I set-up my appointment with them hoping not to waste my time by another "car salesman".

Surprise surprise, when JW heating & air came to my house, it was $2,300 moreover than the quoted $13,500, and that was only IF I was a costco member (15% rewards card), executive member with 2% back, and had the costco Visa card with 2% back! I expected more from a Costco affiliated service!</text>

<Text>About me, I'm a very detail oriented person who must have work done professionally, cleanly and accurately with great attention to aesthetic.  I need straight lines, accurate specs and it MUST LOOK GOOD.  My review is both 5 stars and 3 stars...thus I gave this company a 4.

5 Stars to Joe Howard and his team: Rene (carpenter/stucco), Gus, Miguel, and Adolfo (A/C install).  If you hire JW Heating and Air make sure to schedule Joe Howard and his team for the installation.

Joe is a hard worker, respectful, clean, easy to talk to and no-nonsense about doing a professional job.  If something is wrong, whatever it is, he'll fix it.  He won't try to explain it away.  He sees what you see.  If it's not professionally done he'll make sure to have it re-done and done right.

3 stars to JW Heating and Air because the first team they sent me.  Whoever did the scheduling sent a team who never ever came to my home.  I had to re-explain what was talked about with Joe Howard.  I was stressed the entire day and when they finished I found a ton of aesthetic issues.  And although that team was courteous and nice, they were sometimes loud and laughing while working.  They were a young team, did parts of the job rushed (there was a lot to do bc I never had A/C) and without concern of how it would look.  I had to act as my own contractor and constantly check on them.
At the end of the day there were things done wrong and that did not look good.   I was very unhappy.  On top of it all I was paying a lot of $$$ and I was stressed.  It's not right to be paying so much money, be put in such a stressful position and have to work as my own contractor.  When I hire a professional company I expect them to do the entire job, do it right and make sure I'm happy for the entire process.

On a positive note - JW Heating's Kris - who takes care of the rebates is on top of things and I really appreciate that they took care of all rebate processing for me.

And at the end of the day, I was very happy with how the job was completed.

The Bottom Line - Make sure to have Joe Howard at your walk through and make sure the scheduler knows you must have him.  Even if you have to wait another week or two.

Thank you Joe Howard and Team!

< date>
1475938381568</date>
<Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
I highly recommend JW Heating and Air.  We completely replaced our furnace, AC unit, and all ductwork.

I met with 3 HVAC folks and was very disappointed with them.  They all immediately sized the system without doing the Manual J calc, based on my home's square footage.  I knew from my research on the web that this is completely wrong.

I turned to Angie's list and found JW Heating and Air had over 1,000 A ratings, and figured we'd try them out.  Ted Ceausu from JW Heating and Air was great to work with. Very professional and before he left, said he'd be doing the manual J calculations and then room calcs to figure out the amount of air-flow and duct size we would need in each room.

Woohoo!  I didn't even need to ask about it!

Their cost was right in the middle between the lowest and highest bids I received.  But everything Ted said, was great. We have a home built in 1936, and he is experience working with other historic homes and provided us a vendor for reproduction grates that he was able to include in our quote.

But it's really the attention to details that made all the difference.  Since antique style grates have much bigger openings, he let us know that they would spray paint the inside of the registers black to ensure we wouldn't see any silver metal when looking inside.  This compared to my neighbor who said that when she asked her HVAC installer to do the same, he said his job stopped at the installation. She had to paint her own.

The crew was all very polite and they kept our house very clean as all new holes needed to be cut for all the registers as the existing ones were too small or not well-placed.

Best of all, when the state inspector came, he said our 5-ton system was the best he'd every tested as far as leakage, at 4 1/2%.   Avoid any contractor who doesn't want you to get permits or inspections.  Paying for that is like money in-the-bank over the long haul to insure your systems was installed properly.

We've had the system for two weeks, and so-far-so good with the AC.

Again, JW Heating and AIR is the best!< /review>

< Text>
Jeff and his team are a simply fantastic and I could not recommend them enough.  We got a number of bids from different places. Jeff‚Äôs estimate was not the cheapest, but very reasonable, and his bid felt the most thorough and honest.  He spent over two and a half hours at the house, looking around the attic, and the entire house.  He made his suggestions, and talked us through what would take place.  He said it would take about three days‚Äîbtw, one of the bids told us it would take one day, which I see now would have been impossible).  They were removing all of the ductwork and replacing it with new ducts everywhere, installing all new vents and creating a brand new vent, moving the AC to the roof, an putting in an entirely new furnace in the attic, and creating an up to code drainage system. We ultimately went with Lennox for our HVAV and a Mitsubishi mini split for the outside studio.

Thanks Jeff,
